She saw the vision of DeL's request in the temple. And then appeared beside her as the RoC princess headed back to the village.  In her arms she held her newly born infant who lay quietly sleeping against her bosom.  Hera's pale eyes turned to DeL as she had quietly appeared.  One hand reached out and gently touched DeL's forearm. <br>
&quot;My child, you shall never bare.  You have my promise and blessing,&quot; she looked to DeL tenderly and sadly. &quot;I am sorry this has happened.  Know I will do what I can to help you out of this.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sartha>Sartha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#993300>(6/4/01 3:14:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=219.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ::left with Dawnie::</span><hr size=1> ::she watched DeL leave with a soft smile:: Anytime, Athelfi... anytime... <br>
